PostDoc position: Semantic Web and CIDOC CRM for supporting the=20
scientific study of heritage objects and buildings

University of Tours, LIFAT and CITERES-LAT, Tours and Blois, France

This postdoctoral position takes place within the French ANR SESAMES=20
project (S=E9mantisation Et Spatialisation d=92Artefacts patrimoniaux=20
Multi-Echelles : annotation 3D, Sonification et formalisation du=20
raisonnement). The aim of this project is to provide methodological and=20
technical tools for supporting the scientific study of heritage objects=20
and buildings, in particular to assist the discovery of relationships=20
and the explicitation of scientific reasoning. One important dimension=20
the project aims to devise and use, is a semantic model based on one or=20
several ontologies for representing the domain data and knowledge.

The position responsibilities include:
- Deep understanding of CIDOC CRM, an ontology for cultural heritage=20
data, with its extensions dedicated to archaeology (CRMarchaeo),=20
scientific observations (CRMsci), building archaeology (CRMba) and=20
scientific reasoning (CRMInf).
- Deep understanding of the different modes and scales of observations=20
about the given archaeological site.
- Mapping of existing data to their semantic counterparts.
- Operationalizing the ontologies and semantic datasets to support=20
scientific works on heritage objects and buildings.

Requirements
The candidate holds a PhD related to Semantic Web technologies,=20
knowledge representation and knowledge engineering. He or she is able to =

combine theoretical and practical aspects in his/her work. French and/or =

English communication skills are required. Software development skills=20
are also mandatory (with Jena or RDF4J libraries). It would be a plus if =

the candidate had some experiences of collaborating with scholars in the =

humanities.

Duration: 12 months, start as soon as possible
Salary: approximately 2000 =80 / month (net)
